race.comment: The $3 million 2YO Classic. I'm siding with one of the local hopes in ZIP LOCK (1), who is yet to taste defeat in two career outings including a strong win in the BJ McLachlan last time out. Racing high on confidence and is expected to measure up again, particularly with the scratching of the early favourite. TORNADO VALLEY (2) finished second behind ZIP LOCK last time out and the two Victorian runs prior were full of merit. Looks ready to explode on the back of his performance in the McLachlan and he can play a major role. UNIT FIVE (5) was well supported at Caulfield on debut and didn't let backers down saluting in dominant fashion. Hard to ignore. SHIKI (7) next best out of the astute yard for 2YO's.
